I got an error like this
error: cannot convert 'const MetaPhysicL::SemiDynamicSparseNumberArray<double, long unsigned int, MetaPhysicL::NWrapper<500> >' to 'MooseADWrapper<double, false>' {aka 'double'} in assignment _gap_conductance_dT[_qp] =cache_conductance.derivatives();
I hope to get your help!

For example, for h_radiation(), I added AD keyword, compared with the original MOOSE
ADReal
GasGapConductance::h_radiation()
{
  if (_emissivity == 0.0)
    return 0.0;

  ADReal surface_integration_factor = 1.0;

  if (_gap_geometry_type == GasGapConductance::CYLINDER)
    surface_integration_factor = 0.5 * (_r1 + _r2) / _radius;
  else if (_gap_geometry_type == GasGapConductance::SPHERE)
    surface_integration_factor = 0.25 * (_r1 + _r2) * (_r1 + _r2) / (_radius * _radius);

  const ADReal temp_func =
      (_temp[_qp] * _temp[_qp] + _gap_temp * _gap_temp) * (_temp[_qp] + _gap_temp);

  return _stefan_boltzmann * temp_func / _emissivity * surface_integration_factor;
}

error: cannot convert 'const MetaPhysicL::SemiDynamicSparseNumberArray<double, long unsigned int, MetaPhysicL::NWrapper<500> >' to 'MooseADWrapper<double, false>' {aka 'double'} in assignment _gap_conductance_dT[_qp] =cache_conductance.derivatives();

means you are trying to implicitly convert from an ADReal to a Real.
The material property is probably declared as a Real

Thank you for your answer, I think I have achieved what I wanted to do, maybe not the recommended way to achieve. I used ChainedReal,
const GenericChainedReal<true> cache_temp =GenericChainedReal<true>(_temp[_qp], 1);
 const GenericChainedReal<true> cache_conductance=  h_radiation(cache_temp);
_gap_conductance[_qp] =  cache_conductance.value().value();
_gap_conductance_dT[_qp] =cache_conductance.derivatives().value();

GenericChainedReal<true>
GasGapConductance::h_radiation(const GenericChainedReal<true> & temp)
{
  if (_emissivity == 0.0)
    return GenericChainedReal<true>(0, 0);
  ADReal surface_integration_factor = 1.0;
  const GenericChainedReal<true> temp_func =
      (temp * temp + _gap_temp * _gap_temp) * (temp + _gap_temp);
  return _stefan_boltzmann * temp_func / _emissivity * surface_integration_factor;
}

